# **4. Fibonacci using DP**

The Fibonacci sequence is one of the simplest examples of Dynamic Programming.
In normal recursion, the same values are calculated multiple times, increasing
complexity exponentially. DP stores previous values and avoids repeated 
computation. This reduces complexity from O(2ⁿ) to O(n).

### Example

F(n)=F(n-1)+F(n-2)

For:

```id="7"
F(5)
```

Calculation:

```id="8"
F(5) = F(4) + F(3)
     = 3 + 2
     = 5
```

