# **5. 0/1 Knapsack Problem**

The 0/1 Knapsack Problem is used to maximize profit while keeping weight within 
capacity. Each item can either be selected or not selected. DP is used to store 
maximum profit values for different capacities. This problem is important 
in resource allocation, budgeting, and cargo management.

### Example

Items:

| Item | Weight | Value |
| ---- | ------ | ----- |
| A    | 1      | 10    |
| B    | 3      | 40    |
| C    | 4      | 50    |

Bag Capacity = 4

Best choice:

```id="9"
A + B = 50
```

DP Formula:
dp[i][w]=\max(value[i]+dp[i-1][w-weight[i]],\ dp[i-1][w])

