# **7. Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS)**

LIS finds the longest subsequence where elements are in increasing order. 
Elements need not be consecutive. DP checks previous elements and 
updates maximum subsequence length.

### Example

Array:

```id="15"
[10, 22, 9, 33, 21, 50]
```

LIS:

```id="16"
10, 22, 33, 50
```

Length:

```id="17"
4
```

DP Concept:

```id="18"
If arr[i] > arr[j]
then update LIS length
```

