# **8. Matrix Chain Multiplication (MCM)**

Matrix Chain Multiplication determines the minimum number of operations needed to multiply matrices.
Different multiplication orders require different costs.
DP helps choose the minimum cost order.

### Example

Matrices:

```id="19"
A = 10×20
B = 20×30
C = 30×40
```

Two ways:

```id="20"
(AB)C
A(BC)
```

Minimum cost is selected using DP.

Formula:
dp[i][j]=\min(dp[i][k]+dp[k+1][j]+cost)

